reviews.title: Welcoming!
reviews.text: The bidding was super welcoming, the food was delicious and served warmly and when it started raining we moved from outside to inside at a more than fine bar.

reviews.title: Delicious food!
reviews.text:
Great food, nice cozy place.
Could see the cook busy, always good, an open kitchen!

Very tasty, nicely made up and the price was neat!

reviews.title: Great!!
reviews.text: What a lovely place, super friendly staff, just for coffee and cake. Good coffee and presentation of the pastry looked very nice. (Took a bite though😅)

reviews.title: It is worth repeating
reviews.text: We were very kindly welcomed by an attentive Customer gentleman. On the menu are some more original dishes than average. We chose the vegetarian curry. It was delicious. It's worth repeating.
We were only allowed to sit at a small table for dinner after requesting a fairly large table where two people were just sitting so inflexible that that was not allowed. Unfriendly and inflexible.

reviews.title: Glad to go back over and over
reviews.text: If you are in Harlingen, friendly place with terrific food. Never been on a very busy moment so cannot confirm or deny remarks of other reviewers about the service then. But for us 5 out of 5.

reviews.title: Great food top service
reviews.text: Delicious outdoor dining. Super nice service. Smoothly got our desired food. Great taste, local ingredients. not too much and not too little. Also smooth with solution for allergies. Super nice property in the heart of Harlingen. Great!!!

reviews.title: Incredibly good - you must have experienced this!
reviews.text: One of my best restaurant visits!! Incredibly good service and extremely friendly and attentive service. Great food - we are absolutely thrilled ! Thanks for the great evening at your place!

reviews.title: Revelation!
reviews.text: Spontaneous visit without any prior knowledge. What a revelation! Superb property, genuine hospitality, creative menu and neat prices. A lot of restaurants could learn from it.

reviews.title: Highly recommended!
reviews.text:
A cozy eatery in a nice building, good atmosphere, delicious fish eaten and top girls in the service! 
Highly recommended!

reviews.title: TOP Local
reviews.text: Probably one of the best places I visited in the Netherlands. We had 2 very great fish dishes, a very good mackerel starter and a super dessert. Everything prepared very tasty. Staff very friendly. Wine (riesling) delicious.

reviews.title: Very tasty!
reviews.text: Beautiful old ambiance, very tasty bread🍞 as before, the main course was for both, fish and meat, and the sides were just top, could have done with a little more time in between, but was delicious, highly recommended!

reviews.title: Top spot! Do it.
reviews.text: That's the way it should be. Everything is right here, lovely people, really good food, nicely made up, nice prices. In a beautiful property too. Here one understands what the hospitality experience must be like. The guest is first, bottle of water on the table, top. 2 days later cup of coffee done with apple pastry. Also such a nice experience. So don't hesitate: you can enter here without any hesitation! Or outside.. also beautiful.

reviews.title: Very good food
reviews.text:
Cozy eatery! Nicely decorated, smooth friendly service. Also bring to the children very attentively immediately a high chair , drawing and colors. Good food everything was very well taken care of. Super experience! 

It is now the 3rd time that we come to Harlingen (spread over a few years) every time at Nooitgedagt eat very good!

reviews.title: Super good food!
reviews.text: This place is great to eat! Super tasty! And super friendly service! We'll be back for sure! This will be our little restaurant in Harlingen!

reviews.title: Good food 👊
reviews.text: Joined for lunch with the family in Nooitgedacht. Friendly staff and great food. The bound fish soup and the homemade Icetea are highly recommended.

reviews.title: Highly recommended!
reviews.text: Highly recommended! Super tasty and refined food with great friendly service. Very quiet and beautiful setting. If you are in Harlingne, definitely do!

reviews.title: Nice location, friendly staff, with delicious food
reviews.text:
For starters, what a most friendly welcome! Choice in where we wanted to sit, downstairs or upstairs!
Delicious dishes, super wines!
In a word.... Great!

reviews.title: Super nice restaurant in fantastic beautiful building in the center of beautiful Harlingen.
reviews.text:
After visiting Christmas market eaten at Nooitgedacht. Nice place on the floor and great food. The short rib is recommended. Just looked at google, some laborious meat! Is more than worth the price!
The turbot was also gentlemanly.
This in combination with friendly fun service completes the evening!

reviews.title: Tosti  ‘fantastico’
reviews.text:
Fantastic lunch eaten; Toastie with basil-humus-grilled vegetables- mozzarella and pesto.
Just added to the new menu and highly recommended and definitely to come back for.

reviews.title: Delicious food in atmospheric atmosphere
reviews.text: We had a lovely lunch in Nooitgedagt. There was gluten-free bread for my wife and also gluten-free cakes. Original menu, tasteful decor and friendly and personal service, highly recommended!

reviews.title: Recommended: before or after the boat to Terschelling!
reviews.text: Nice, beautiful place! Very draughty and noisy though! Table next door is therefore actually not to use! Such a shame.... Food was good and service helpful and friendly!

reviews.title: Fantastic dinner and atmosphere. Very kind service too. The place is particular with a corner with some toys for kids.
reviews.text: All the plates we tried were very good and well displayed too. Nice to see the kitchen as you eat. Waiting time was normal. Really a small gem in this beautiful town! Deserves a visit!

reviews.title: Lovely welcoming terrace with ditto coffee and cake
reviews.text: Very nice spacious terrace. Bottle of water is waiting for you on the table upon arrival, even during the day if you come for coffee. Big plus! Nice smooth service, nice coffee with cakes. If we ever visit Harlingen again we will definitely be back.

reviews.title: One of the best locations
reviews.text: We stayed a total of three times for dinner at Nooitgedagt. Great atmosphere, super friendly and attentive service (unparalleled in Harlingen) and fantastic food. Play area for the children and finally motivated service staff who know how to bring the great food from the kitchen to the woman/man. Keep it up, you're a great team!

reviews.title: Great lunch, super menu and prices
reviews.text: We were here 5 years ago following a trip advisor review, today just as great as then. Super lunch place with unique sandwiches at a very good price, coffee was also super. Next time we are in Harlingen we will be back

reviews.title: Beautiful restaurant
reviews.text: What a beautiful place this is, great food, beautiful original menu and fine service. The prices are very reasonable and it is a very attractive hotel in a beautiful old building.

reviews.title: Welcoming and delicious
reviews.text: It was super busy but the hostess was very inventive and had arranged a nice table in no time after we had a drink at the bar

reviews.title: Not well cooked, not affordable
reviews.text: The raw materials were not well handled. The spring chicken was tasteless and had pale, chewy and fuzzy skin. Low flavors, dull sky sauces. A small undressed salad was served with the meal. On the table was certainly a container that said olive oil, but inside was instead some cheap, neutral oil. On the plus side there are nice staff and environment, but overall it is not affordable.

reviews.title: Great cafe
reviews.text: What a fantastic cafe staff were excellent and the owners design flair is wonderful it’s the little touches that make the difference. The presentation of the food showed the care and passion of the place. Highly recommend a visit

reviews.title: Enjoy a tasty meal at Nooitgedagt
reviews.text: I ate a delicious cheese fondue, and it was surrounded by delicious vegetables, potatoes, fresh bread, nuts, greens. I cheated. Highly recommended.

reviews.title: Super delicious for years!
reviews.text: We have been here several times during our many sailing trips. Very good food, very nice atmosphere, top staff! Always happy to come back!

reviews.title: Great restaurant
reviews.text: Wonderful food, friendly, attentive service and a pleasant atmosphere. We can highly recommend Nooitgedacht.

reviews.title: Surprisingly tasty combinations from the chef!
reviews.text: Great place for a surprising meal. We had lunch there twice. You won't find the combinations that the chef makes elsewhere. Nice staff. Nice play area for children downstairs. The space upstairs is fine, but the steep stairs to the top are not suitable for everyone. Cozy terrace on the side. Nice spacious toilet room.

tips.body: Houdt rekening met de steile trap naar boven.

reviews.title: Very ordinary
reviews.text: First time never thought about it after good reviews here. It is hard to see why it is so high on our list. Staff is friendly, atmosphere is sparse. We ordered two fish dishes, sea bream was sooo small, you really shouldn't serve it as a main dish. Side dishes, potatoes and salad are tasteless. I would definitely change something.

reviews.title: Dinner in Harlingen
reviews.text:
Discovered by chance.
A wonderful evening, with such friendly and competent service.
Great food in a nice atmosphere.
Many thanks to the team 👍🏻

reviews.title: Book and enjoy!
reviews.text:
Pleasant. Nice knowledgeable service AND delicious food!
We ate the bavette with asparagus. Was great! And the dessert party was also yum.

reviews.title: A really nice restaurant
reviews.text:
A really nice restaurant. 
The food was good, apart from the slightly over-salted fish, which my wife had. Otherwise everything was very good.

reviews.title: From Zeehoeve campsite in Harlingen to Terschelling. When we returned to Harlingen we looked for a restaurant.
reviews.text: After a crossing from Terschelling to Harlingen and a tip from someone, we looked up Nooitgedagt. It has a pleasant, casual atmosphere and it was nice and full and the food was good. Nice, smooth, young service. So highly recommended.

reviews.title: Super cozy and delicious
reviews.text: Super friendly and good service. Food looks good and tastes very good. In other words: a real tip if you are in the area.

reviews.title: Great place for something to drink and eat after strolling through beautiful Harlingen.
reviews.text: Tea and coffee with cakes done. Very nice location. Everything could be a little smoother, but delicious coffee and tea, delicious pastries where a lot of attention is also paid to the layout. Nice staff, nice place.

reviews.title: All very good!
reviews.text: We found this restaurant and went to it one evening for dinner. Each course was exquisite. The appetizer with noodles was excellent and the guinea fowl was also excellent. The idea of bringing a plate with a taste of all the desserts to share between 2 is nice.

reviews.title: Delicious food. Trendy location. Very nice service. Very good value for money.
reviews.text: A really great experience all around. Starting with the good styling of the location, through the really creative, delicious food to the nice service. A really exceptionally good price-performance ratio. The cuisine is modern, creative, fresh, i.e. not the heavy food that is still common in Holland. The wine was really nice for the price and the service was warm, friendly, good!!!

reviews.title: A restaurant with a soul
reviews.text:
Yes, a great experience, the atmosphere and especially the care of the staff!!
The service was so friendly and breath taking.
The food made with so much care.
Highly recommended.
Keep it up, in one word great!!

reviews.title: Eatery?
reviews.text: Ate at Christmas. Basically fine, but not very special. A menu that has been kept minimal (3 fish, 3 meat and 2 vegetarian main courses). Service very good and friendly and many home-made items including iced tea. Basically fine, but the dishes and portions are not too large, while Nooitgedacht profiles itself as an eatery. We are not big eaters, but if you are not full after three courses, you are not a diner.

reviews.title: Super fun evening and delicious food!
reviews.text: Had a super nice evening. Food was delicious and the service was very friendly and attentive. Everything with a smile. Dishes were great, including vegetarian options! Ambience also nice.

reviews.title: Beautiful historic place with excellent food
reviews.text: Wonderful restaurant, affordable and a beautiful place. The building is beautiful. Nice service, we sat upstairs with a view of the kitchen. Awesome.

reviews.title: close to perfection...
reviews.text:
what an experience, almost perfect in every way. I don't come across this often. There is almost always some negatives to write down, but not now!
The dinner:
We both go for a starter:
my lord of the table:
Mustard, watercress, apple cream soup: very successful (€6.25)
Myself:
Slowly cooked pork belly - Shiitake broth
quail egg noodles beech mushroom, delicious... (€12.50)

Main dish:
My lord of the table:
Guinea fowl, pumpkin cream, beech mushroom.. could have been a little more juicy, but the whole thing was a very big 8..!
Myself:
one-pan dish of Frisian beef stew with mashed potatoes with Frisian dry sausage... (can be left out, as far as I'm concerned) a big 8.5

The whole of both is a beautiful balance of fine flavors and composed details.
Overall I can only conclude that these menus taste fantastic.

The wine (white) that we order in consultation with the restaurant lady (owner?) also fits perfectly with these dishes, a Monte Porzio from the Catone region. (€25 per bottle)

The service/staff also deserves a separate mention:
We really have no comments whatsoever about the way our dinner and experience was supervised by the staff.
On the background. but always nearby and alert.

The location and the ambiance/interior also put you straight into a relaxed and atmospheric mode.

Dear Nooitgedagt, many can follow this example.
Almost everything perfect, except for one thing:
When guests come in and you sit in the front, you always feel the cold outside, despite the double doors... a small thing, but I still had to worry about something...
Chapeau..!!

A big 8.5

reviews.title: Ambiance and great food!
reviews.text: Lovely lunch in a beautiful building from the 1600s.  The staff was very friendly and spoke excellent English.   The food and drinks were all delicious.  We had a vegan with us who found also had a great choice on the menu.   The ambiance was so nice that we ended up staying for hours.    Highly recommend this restaurant.

reviews.title: Lekkkkkkerrrrrrr…..
reviews.text:
Delicious food, the restaurant looks very nice and the service is so nice.
Nice with white cotton tablecloths.
A top restaurant

reviews.title: Beautiful restaurant in a beautiful setting
reviews.text: Nice restaurant in old warehouse. Super friendly service. The fish dishes were good but lacked a bit of finesse. We had ray with capers in a cream sauce, but the capers and sauce were hard to find. The stairs to the top floor are very steep!

reviews.title: Recommended
reviews.text: Nice and cozy terrace! Friendly and helpful staff! Food was delicious too. Definitely recommended for a nice lunch.

reviews.title: When in Harlingen make this your dinner destination
reviews.text: Superb restaurant with delicious food, great wines and local  beers on tap, outstanding service from the staff and a beautiful building . If you are in Harlingen this should be  on top of your list as a great dinner venue.

reviews.title: Make an appointment if you can
reviews.text:
Maybe one of the best restaurants with a limited choice of menu. Average pricing.
To sit inside you should make an appointment  I suggest. Outside is very cosely but can be chilly.

reviews.title: Very nice spot to sit
reviews.text: For years already a very nice spot to sit and eat. Also great to sit with kids, staff is so nice for them.

reviews.title: Great food, great hostess
reviews.text:
Really nice restaurant in the centre of Harlingen Netherlands, with lovely friendly staff. Enjoyed my meal and the company of the hostess, lovely woman, although her Irish accent was more Indian sounding 🤣

Very good value for money too, which is always nice to see 👍

reviews.title: Go for it
reviews.text:
This is a restaurant which has enough good staff working and sertenly give people a feeling being welcome and not just another number.
The menu isn't that big, but also here less is more.
Quality food was perfect.
Complimentary water fresh with mint and drinks yummy.

reviews.title: Excellent
reviews.text: Tonight I had dinner here, without reservation but I thankfully could be seated at the bar. The staff were really kind and attentive, they made me feel very welcome and taken care of. As I was dining alone,  I appreciated this even more. The menu was perfect; I ordered red bass with a good amount of well prepared sidedishes and a lovely organic, green white Spanish dry wine. I highly recommend this place for anyone appreciating good food in a warm atmosphere.

reviews.title: Wonderful
reviews.text:
Great place to have lunch or diner. The large staff are very sympathetic, patient, flexible and attentive. The customers are kings and queens here. 
I can recommend the smoked eel as starter and the whole sea bass as main course. Also the salads are rich and tasteful. 
Not to be missed when you visit Harlingen.

reviews.title: Beautiful decoration and tasty food
reviews.text:
We went to this place for lunch and it was great. We ordered a bouillabaisse which was stunning, and a lunch platter which was also nice.
We loved the look and feel of the place and the atmosphere.

reviews.title: A nice place, with good food and a welcoming staff
reviews.text: We had a reservation in advance, and were promptly seated. The menus were swiftly provided,and the specials chalkboard pointed out.  The only delay encountered was some discussion about what we'd have as an aperitif. Our party of four selected three different mains, all off the specials board. We were all satisfied with our selections, and very pleased to find such a nice place. Note: it's nice to see an "old fashioned veg" like parsnips being featured in dishes.

reviews.title: Charming workers, warming place
reviews.text:
Rose gave us the best possible service. Wewere 2 couples and a child. We ordered some delicious soups, salad, croquettes and hamburguers. They had an special menu for children and a lovely place with toys for them.

Good food at good price. If we came back to Harlingen, we'll come back to visit them.

reviews.title: Great informal restaurant
reviews.text:
Probably the best place to eat in Harlingen if you don’t want to be too formal. Good quality/price ratio. 
Creative menu with a combination of Dutch and international dishes. 
The service is better than most places and they everyone with full attention (as far I could see during my visit).

reviews.title: Delicious food well served
reviews.text: On a rainy evening after the main tourist period, when we were despairing of finding anywhere to eat, we found this restaurant open and serving an excellent choice of perfectly-cooked food. The menu had a large selection and the friendly and  knowledgeable staff made us feel very welcome.

reviews.title: Really lovely lunch in the center of Harlingen
reviews.text: Very charming cafe in an old building, cafe has a vintage/homemade flair. We enjoyed sandwiches and homemade ice tea (but no ice). The Lebanese bread sandwich was especially good. The desserts looked amazing but we were out of time.

reviews.title: Nice location for a small dinner
reviews.text:
I ate her last friday while visiting Harlingen for a wedding. I didn't had any reservations, so with a full restaurant I was offered a place at the bar. Which I took.

I had quite a good dinner which arrived quickly after I ordered. So no complaints there. Also the price wasn't bad - 30 euros for the dinner; two bears and a coffee.

But the place at the bar did made me notice things. It was a mess behind the bar - something of an organized chaos. There was not a lot of overview or structure for the personnel as well: who is doing what? And I also thought the location was pretty noisy. Tables are close together, and the whole of the room did reflect the noise. 

Bottomline: good dinner, nice price, but rethink if you would like a romantic dinner for two.

reviews.title: Outstanding
reviews.text: Compliments to the crew, great experience. We ate here twice on our way to and from Terschelling. Great food, great atmosphere and super friendly and competent team.

reviews.title: Excellent food with best service
reviews.text: Quality wise at high level. Personel is friendly, knowledgeable and fast. Great dinner highly recommended to anyone visiting the city

reviews.title: The Best Local Cafe in Harlingen!
reviews.text: Nooitgedadgt is a great cafe set in a wine warehouse built in 1647. They still use a block and tackle to bring food up from the pavement to the kitchen on the top floor. Apart from the really good food selections, the staff are what makes this cafe the best in town. All of them speak really good english and they make you feel welcome and they are able to recognize you after a couple of visits.  The coffee is also excellent and they can make the coffee that you prefer - they understand what a Long Black with a jug of fresh milk on the side looks like without the lenghthy explanation that is never understood. In our view this is a must visit if you are in Harlingen and you will not be disappointed.

reviews.title: Lunch
reviews.text: Lovely welcoming young staff. Very busy as not many tables indoors but was offered a drink at the bar whilst waiting.  Also had the choice to eat at the bar if wanted but we waited for a table and were not disappointed with the food.  Very tasty and lots of it.

reviews.title: Great food in nice atmpsphere
reviews.text:
We had lunch here when we came of the ferry from Terschelling. The restaurant is nicely decorated and has a good atmosphere. Nice laid back music, friendly staff and many teas. We had a starter platter to share and the soup of the day. All very tasty and fresh. The coffee afterwards was als very good.

Highly recommended for lunch in Harlingen.

reviews.title: Great Atmosphere
reviews.text: Went there for a birthday lunch with family. Loved the jazz and old classic music. Food was good - we all liked it. Lunch menu was limited, but the soups and salads we had were all good.

reviews.title: Top location!
reviews.text: The place is in the center in near the haven for the ships, so it's strategic. It's an historic building and inside it's rustic and you will feel at home. The guy who served as was very kind and Professional but he was the only one in the place and it's difficult to manage everything alone. There is also a beutiful but big terrace. The food was nice and so was the price.

reviews.title: I always come here when in Harlingen
reviews.text:
Working backwards:
They make their own after dessert mints!
The dessert was amazing, something typically Dutch, made with egg whites and fruit, with tons of fresh fruit and grated Graham’s   So yummy and not feeling guilty
The main course was described as pork with “force meat of shrimp” it was a pork steak with prawns (whole) in a sauce that was really nice. Served with mashed potatoes AND the best FRENCH fries I’ve ever had. They were thick and cut in came profile as a celery stick so they were crispy but soft on inside. The slaw was made from pickled smoked golden beets and was out of this world. Also served with stewed rhubarb. 
The starter I had was “Red Baron” cheese melted Ot he a blini. Nice flavor and texture. 
The staff are really friendly and always accompanied me no matter when I show up. There is real care shown in their food with fresh ingredients and novel preparation. I hop I get back again, their food is great

reviews.title: Perfect experience
reviews.text:
Great lovely service, smiling, fast and efficient staff. Food was very very good, served with pride. Portions are big, prices are moderate. 
It was a very enjoyable experience and would eat here again. 
Try it! It’s a great restaurant

reviews.title: Great place
reviews.text: Visited here on our travels.  The waitress took our drinks order and we asked for the food menu.  On bringing it she had realised we were English and explained it was only In Dutch but It if we needed translation assistance just to her. We ordered and asked a couple of questions which she answered in good English.  Our food arrived swiftly and was really tasty and good value for money,  the waitress checked with us everything was ok and was also quick to realise when we had finished, came and took our plates and asked if we wanted anything else.  We were too full up so just asked for the bill, which again came swiftly, paid and Departed to continue our travels.  Great food, great place, great service, we would go back again,

reviews.title: Oasis for Hungry Travelers
reviews.text: We were looking for a restaurant in Harlingen where we could get some fresh fish for dinner, and Eetcafe Nooitgedagt was indeed the perfect spot.  The Sea Bass was excellent, as was the Pumpkin Parsnip soup.  Great seafood appetizers!  The waitress was very helpful with the menu options and the service was great.  I went in a little hangry and left happy and satiated.

reviews.title: Great food, great service.
reviews.text:
Visited with a group of friends for dinner. We didn't have a reservation, but they gave us a wonderful window table.
The food was great; the sea-food excellent and the steaks were extra tender!
Our waiter was knowledgeable, attentive and friendly and we had a great time!

reviews.title: Great food (also for celiacs)!
reviews.text: I had a great lunch here: everything tasted amazing and they were even able to cater to our gluten free wishes. The pastrami on gluten free bread with a substituted red port syrup was amazing (we wanted a bottle of the syrup it was so good). This will be our new staple for when we're in the neighbourhood.

reviews.title: Great informal restaurant
reviews.text:
Probably the best place to eat in Harlingen if you don’t want to be too formal. Good quality/price ratio. Creative menu with a combination of Dutch and international dishes. 
The service is better than most places and they everyone with full attention (as far I could see during my visit).

reviews.title: A nice visit on a Thursday afternoon
reviews.text: We came here together with my boyfriend and his family. Everything was great - the food, the drinks, the atmosphere.. Definitely recommend when visiting Harlingen.

reviews.title: I did not expect this, but it was fantastic
reviews.text: Middle of February and everything was closed in Harlingen, so walking down the streets looking in to the few open restaurants all of them empty I realized we are out of season , but then here completely full , great went in and very friendly reception, yes we have a table have a drink in the bar and we make it ready , it was just totally surprised, I did not expect, the placed at the table we I chose a zeebarse, and it was served on some Kinde of peer pure? And orange lemonade , never tasted this mixture, I really didn’t expect but it was fantastic, really nice to be challenged and surprised, and price was really fair.

reviews.title: Restaurant in de middle of historical city-center
reviews.text: Friendly people, good food. This is one of the restaurant in Harlingen you can visit easy. A very old historical building, where you can have a good meal,

reviews.title: Excellent
reviews.text: Looking for a restaurant with amazing food and great stuff in Harlingen? We can absolutely recommend this super nice, cosy and well furnished restaurant im Harlingen

reviews.title: Great ambiance, great service and definitely good food
reviews.text:
With some places all comes together; the food they serve is delicious and at a reasonable price. They also try some daring combinations of tastes, but it always simply tastes great. 

The hosts are friendly and also the ambiance is great and relaxed!

reviews.title: Overall good (not very good) - service could have been quicker
reviews.text:
There are lots of cafes and restaurants in Harlingen to choose from. We chose Nooitgedagt. Overall it was good enough, the food was tasty however the service could have been quicker. I only realised after checking the menu afterwards that my salad had been missing the olives..... 
Even though it was warm outside we choose to sit inside due to the ants on the tables outside!

reviews.title: Used to be our favourite in Harlingen...
reviews.text:
When making the reservation, I requested for a candle on the dessert as my partner was celebrating his b'day - this was confirmed on the phone (with a fire cracker), and knowing this restaurant from 3 previous visits to Harlingen, we were looking forward to our Sunday evening dinner!

We were seated promptly and our orders came swiftly.
For appetizers we had a small salad (which had more hazelnuts rather than anything else) and the homemade pate, which did not look appetizing in colour/texture and taste was okay due to the nice dressing on the plate, but actually rather disappointing.

Main course was a slow-cooked porkneck and Cod Fish. Pork was so dry that we only ate half and the cod fish combination with noodles was not what we expected.
When mentioning this to the female staff that cleared our plates, she was very snappy and immediately mentioned that we should have said something when she checked with us during the meal... however no one ever came to our table, so we could not mention anything, and we also walked to the kitchen counter ourselves to request for some more mayonnaise (as service was too busy to notice us).

My partner already wanted to leave right after this rude behaviour, but I thought to still be able to surprise him with a nice dessert with a b'day candle... Unfortunately this little gesture was forgotten as well... dessert was the nicest of the evening, but we left very disappointed and will unfortunately not return on a future visit to Harlingen.

Service recovery/apologies is a very simple thing but often unfortunately not taken care of.

reviews.title: Nice for lunch
reviews.text: We ate lunch here, it was very good, they offered good choices to my son who has food allergies. Our salads were delicious. The ambiance is cozy. I highly recommend this eetcafe.

reviews.title: Excellent food and service
reviews.text:
Went with a friend who lives in Harlingen and said this was the best restaurant in town.  I have no reason to doubt him!

It's a lovely building both inside and out and the food was first class.

reviews.title: Nice food nice service
reviews.text: We had a great meal and the service was excellent! very good price quality value and in a nice old building

reviews.title: Excellent
reviews.text: Not the same standards (good or ambience) as t'herologement in the harbour, but a friendly little restraint with a good but slightly limited menu. We ate there several times and would recommend it.

reviews.title: Very nice!!
reviews.text: Very great restaurant! The food is very delicious and the waiters are very nice and helpful! Really recommend!!非常好的一家餐馆，服务非常周到，菜单是荷兰文的，但是服务生用英文为我们详细解释了，并且推荐了可口的菜。头盘2种面包搭配了6种酱，味道很独特，很有荷兰特色。正餐我们点的是一份鱼和一份排骨，都很好吃。甜点是冰淇凌，酸酸的配上奶油很爽口。非常推荐这家店，价格不贵，服务周到，菜很可口。

reviews.title: Delicious, fresh food
reviews.text: My father and I had dinner in the restaurant and I can heartily recommend the food.  The fish I ate (Dorado) was very fresh and delicious.  The accompaniments were interesting and tasty.  The waitstaff were friendly and efficient.  My father had paling and enjoyed it very much.  You can sit outdoors, which we did as it was such a gorgeous evening.  The restaurant is located in a beautiful old building.  We enjoyed it all very much.

reviews.title: Unexpected?
reviews.text: Well, not unexpected, there are some good restaurants in every town, especially Harlingen, but this one - unexpectedly - stands out. From the outside it's your average looking restaurant, but step inside and the cosy atmosphere immediately makes you feel at home. And so does the personnel. Of course there is soom room outside too, but due to it lying next to a busy street and in a Dutch climate, you might prefer the inside. The food is way above average, small amuses making you wanting to eat more all the time. The price is acceptable as well. Thumbs up!

reviews.title: Little Gem
reviews.text: Having a Dutch wife means she expects high standards in a restaurant and this certainly met them. I had spare ribs very different to the swamped bbq UK version. Really tasty with a great sauce on the side. Excellent wine and great friendly service. What more do you want!

reviews.title: Decent lunch
reviews.text: We stopped for a lunch, despite the limited menu offerings due to Tripadvisor good reviews and also since it was less pricey than other restaurants in the area. Overall service was excellent and friendly with good English description of the dishes  on offer. The "inspired" soup of the day, pureed egglplant (aubergine) was way too overseasoned with cumin, and because of the large portion, sort of cloying. The Boullaibaise was pretty light on the seafood and seemed as if it had been reheated quite a few times, despite the fact that it came to the table lukewarm. The sandwich items were better. The one with smoked salmon had fresh, tasty fish, a small bit of salad, and a nice cream cheese addition flavored with lemon. The cheese sandwich which had presliced mittel alter gouda on it was only saved by the relish of caramelized onion and marmelade. Altogether this was not a haut cuisine experience. I would imagine their dinner menu which was more extensive might bring higher praise. It was very thoughtful that they had a play area with toys for kids which would make the restaurant more appealing to families with small children.

reviews.title: Relaxed atmosphere
reviews.text: Enjoyed a very good meal in a stylish but relaxed setting. No English menu but our waitress patiently explained the various dishes.  Leave room for a desert which were excellent. Service was friendly but not rushed. Recommended.

reviews.title: Very good food
reviews.text: The food is very good and fresh. The menu has only a few items but everything is very good and the prices are very decent.

reviews.title: Good food in a nice environment.
reviews.text: This restaurant was one of the only ones open on a Monday in February.  A charming place with good food.  The staff was friendly and helpful. Starters was soup, which was good, HOT, and plentiful.   We both had the zwijnshaasmedallions as our main.  Delicious, hearty meal.  Dessert was Sinaasappel-basilicum hangop met bloedsinaasappelijs.  An excellent choice and a way to end the meal.

reviews.title: Suprising dishes, loose atmosphere, o.k. prizes
reviews.text: It looks disorganized, with different tables and different chairs, but staff and food are very good. Fresh, regional food in interesting compositions.

reviews.title: Excellent menu for large groups
reviews.text:
I went here with a large group from work. We didn't choose any of the food: we were served with 5 appetisers, small main dishes and deserts. In total we were able to taste about 15 different flavours. Some of them were just reasonable (the deserts were ok and the meat wasn't anything special), but others were surprisingly delicious with unexpected combinations of flavour. I was particularly fond of the appetisers and the fish dishes. 

The environment is cozy and even with the house full the waiters came regularly to our table and were able to serve us fast. 

The only con was that we noticed the dishes were not perfectly clean. We even had to ask for new ones in some cases. But it seems it was an exception, since the last dishes were clean.

reviews.title: fast service, great food, large portions, English language staff
reviews.text: Great place to meet with friends and enjoy a large portion traditional Dutch meal.  The atmosphere was relaxed and that particular afternoon, we were welcomed with entertainment.

reviews.title: If only this restaurant could be replicated everywhere
reviews.text: Eetcafe Nooitgedagt has one of the most nostalgic atmosphere's mixed with excellent cuisine I have ever experienced. It's like it was developed by both a country artist and fine chef. The food choices were excellent and everything made is obviously done with great care in not only the preparation and presentation, but also in the thinking of where the ingredients are coming from. As we ate here, we dreamt about the idea of opening a similar restaurant in our own home as we know there isn't anything even close to being like this there.

reviews.title: Friendly and quality but more suitable for a relaxed visit
reviews.text:
Went there today for lunch as listed #2 in Harlingen BUT although food was good to ok the dirty stained menues, IKEA rugs as table covers with stains and bird poo on them on the seating outside are not warranting that place.

Service was very friendly but slow and not that attentive, food took a while and lunch menue is limited to sandwiches and salads, which wasn't that clear.

Fresh and perfect salad dish, impressive Uitsmijter but dissapointing goat cheese sandwich, small and dry. Again - better in evening with friends relaxed and having a laugh.

All in all 2/5 for today only because it had a grimy look and lunch experience. There are a lot of better places for lunch in Harlingen!

reviews.title: honest good food with excellent service
reviews.text: A friend who lives locally took us here, it's one if his favourite places to eat - and it was easy to see why. It's located in a wonderful historic former wine warehouse, with an unpretentious interior - almost loft-like, only not minimalist, but with consciously mismatched secondhand chairs and rough industrial-looking wooden tables. They have an interestng menu with enough choice, even for vegetarians, and at decent prices. Service is very friendly and helpful. There's a bottle of water on every table. Food tastes fresh and is perfectly cooked, the chefs clearly know their business. And dog owners will be happy to hear that their four-legged friend doesn't have to wait outside. We'd like to return here in the future.

reviews.title: Perfect place, perfect food
reviews.text: Had to catch a boat to the islands and came in with a tight schedule. Staff was very helpful and served our food in time to have time left for a stroll back to the harbor. Food was perfect for the occasion, great fresh fish and many choices for the kids. Will certainly come back!

reviews.title: A gem
reviews.text:
On the wayback home we looked for a not too fancy place for a quick diner and decided on Nooitgedagt. That was a good decision. What a nice place, bright modern interior in a history building, very friendly and accomodative staff and great food.
I started with the charcuterie plate, a nice selection of various cold cuts accompanied with home baked bread and a small salad a dish like one would get in Spain. My main dish was confit of guinea fowl with sauerkraut and red wine saus. The 2 quinea fowl legs were delicous, so tender and the meat falling from the bone, and tasty sauerkraut. The wine saus had not been really necessary, but since it came on the side it did not hinder.
The portions were quite large so we had no appetite for dessert and finished with coffee, that came witha nice selections of sweets.
The bill was €140 for 4 starters and 4 main dishes, a bottle of wine and coffees. A steal!

reviews.title: Whenever in Harlingen, we always come here!
reviews.text: Nooitgedagt encapsulates the best of the Netherlands! Friendly, welcoming, "gezellig" and the food is damn good too! Third time here in four years (en route for Terschelling by ferry). Dinner here (with our well behaved dogs allowed in too) is something we look forward to. See you next year! We loved Anna (in from Leeuwarden from sister restau), Nanne Dirk, Amber and Tam of the service team! 10/10!

reviews.title: What a lovely restaurant.
reviews.text:
When you eat in Holland you have the seat for the night, the service is not McDonalds so, service takes its time but you are not ignored or forgotten.
All the food is excellent and each course is enough for two..With excellent house wine Dog and children friendly, This is not the first time I have been to this  establishment and it still is a very friendly and a comfortable enjoyable eating house.When I was previously there in the winter, it was lovely and warm and the staff made my dog welcome

reviews.title: Loved it!
reviews.text: There is a great atmosphere, and the design of this place is very nice. Every chair is different and there are large Loft- like lamps over the tables, it all looks very original. the staff is friendly, there is a place for children ( very good equipped) and food is very good. We had a great evening.

reviews.title: lovely, friendly, generous
reviews.text:
Nice place, kids friendly (playing area), lovely staff.

We were impressed by the quality of the dishes: large "bistro" menu, executed with lot of care and inventiveness.

Very good price to value

reviews.title: Great!
reviews.text: Cosy restaurant in the center of Harlingen. Both food, service and atmosphere are great. It shows that the very friendly staff enjoys to have you as a guest. Loved the food with 'paling' in à newspaper as a typical Dutch highlight. Go there!
